More than 2,800 identity cards were uncollected from the Busia Huduma Centre, with a few hours left before mass voter registration closed on Sunday.Centre manager Linda Jaleta on Sunday urged residents who applied between November and January to collect their cards so they could register before the deadline.&ldquo;Despite sending text messages to the recipients, most of them have remained adamant. Only those who applied two weeks ago have collected their IDs,&rdquo; she told Busia Agriculture executive Moses Osia, who visited her.Osia thanked Jaleta for her efforts in ensuring residents get their ID cards. Busia woman MP Florence Mutua and other NASA leaders last week camped in Nairobi to ensure the release of 43,000 IDs for the region.